  <!-- BODY -->
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 pb-24 grid grid-cols-12 gap-8">

    <!-- Removed left side labels entirely -->

    <!-- Main narrative -->
    <article class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-8 xl:col-span-7">
      <!-- DESCRIPTION (unique, professional) -->
      <section id="description" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Description</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 muted dropcap">From acne and redness to pigment and skin rejuvenation, Aerolase addresses a wide range of concerns without needles or incisions. Treatments are quick, well‑tolerated, and require minimal aftercare, so you can return to normal activities right away.</p>
        <p class="mt-3 muted">
          It works by temporarily blocking nerve signals to specific muscles, softening lines such as frown lines, forehead creases, and crow’s feet.
          Results develop within a few days and last around 3–4 months, leaving the skin smoother and the appearance refreshed while maintaining natural expressions.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 ataglance">
          <span>Pure formula</span><span>3–4 months</span><span>Non‑surgical</span><span>Natural results</span>
        </div>
        <p class="pullquote">“Smoothed lines, natural movement.”</p>
      </section>

      <div class="my-10 h-px border-t rule"></div>

      <!-- BENEFITS (unchanged from v2) -->
      <section id="benefits" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Benefits</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-10 gap-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 muted"><svg class="icon-check" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 7L10 17l-6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg>Safe and effective for all skin tones (Fitzpatrick I–VI).</div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 muted"><svg class="icon-check" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 7L10 17l-6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg>Minimal discomfort and virtually no downtime.</div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 muted"><svg class="icon-check" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 7L10 17l-6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg>Targets acne, redness, vessels, pigment, and overall rejuvenation.</div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3 muted"><svg class="icon-check" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 7L10 17l-6-6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg>Supports collagen remodeling for smoother, firmer skin.</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="my-10 h-px border-t rule"></div>

      <!-- THE PROCESS (unchanged from v2) -->
      <section id="process" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">The Process</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 timeline space-y-6">
          <div class="tl-step"><div class="tl-badge">1</div><p class="tl-title">Consultation</p><p class="muted mt-1">Assessment of goals and medical history, mapping injection points and confirming candidacy.</p></div>
          <div class="tl-step"><div class="tl-badge">2</div><p class="tl-title">Treatment</p><p class="muted mt-1">Small injections with a fine needle into targeted muscles; procedure usually takes 10–15 minutes.</p></div>
          <div class="tl-step"><div class="tl-badge">3</div><p class="tl-title">Follow‑Up</p><p class="muted mt-1">Results develop in 3–5 days with full effect at 2 weeks. Effects last about 3–4 months.</p></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="my-10 h-px border-t rule"></div>

      <!-- PRE / POST (unchanged from v2) -->
      <section id="care" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Pre and Post‑Treatment Instructions</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10">
          <div><p class="font-medium">Before your visit</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 muted mt-2 space-y-2"><li>Avoid tanning and self‑tanners for 1–2 weeks before treatment; use daily SPF.</li><li>Pause retinoids, AHAs/BHAs, and harsh actives for ~3–5 days unless advised otherwise.</li><li>Avoid blood‑thinning meds/supplements (aspirin, NSAIDs, fish oil, vitamin E) ~7 days if approved by your provider.</li><li>Arrive with clean skin (no makeup, lotion, or perfume on treatment areas).</li></ul>
          </div>
          <div><p class="font-medium">After your visit</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 muted mt-2 space-y-2"><li>Expect mild redness/warmth for a few hours; cool compresses if needed.</li><li>Avoid heat, sauna, and strenuous exercise for 24 hours; resume skincare the next day unless instructed.</li><li>Use gentle cleanser and SPF 30+ daily; limit sun exposure for at least one week.</li><li>Hold retinoids/exfoliants for ~3–5 days post‑treatment or per provider guidance.</li></ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="my-10 h-px border-t rule"></div>

      <!-- FAQs (unchanged from v2) -->
      <section id="faqs" class="measure">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer"><span class="font-medium ml-1">How is Xeomin different from Botox?</span></summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">Its 650‑microsecond delivery concentrates energy in targets while minimizing heat in surrounding skin—enhancing comfort, safety, and suitability for all skin tones.</p></details>
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer"><span class="font-medium ml-1">When will I see results?</span></summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">Common indications include acne and PFB, redness/rosacea and vessels, melasma and hyperpigmentation, skin rejuvenation and tightening, scars and stretch marks, nail fungus, and warts.</p></details>
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer"><span class="font-medium ml-1">How long do results last?</span></summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">Most concerns respond best to a series (e.g., 3–6 sessions spaced 3–4 weeks apart), followed by periodic maintenance. Your plan is customized to your skin and goals.</p></details>
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer"><span class="font-medium ml-1">Is the treatment painful?</span></summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">Downtime is minimal. You may see transient redness or warmth for a few hours; makeup and routine activities usually resume the same day.</p></details>
          <details class="faq"><summary class="flex items-center cursor-pointer"><span class="font-medium ml-1">Are there side effects?</span></summary><p class="muted mt-2 ml-6">Most clients describe a warm, quick sensation. The ultra‑short pulses and 1064 nm wavelength help keep treatments comfortable.</p></details>
        </div>
      </section>
    </article>

    <!-- Right margin notes (sticky cues) remain -->
    
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
